## 3) If you want “pure AI SDK” without the community provider

You can also use `@ai-sdk/openai` pointing at Z.AI **but you MUST force chat mode**, because AI SDK 5 calls the OpenAI *Responses* API by default. ([AI SDK][6])

### Install

```bash
npm i ai @ai-sdk/openai
```

### Provider

```ts
import { createOpenAI } from '@ai-sdk/openai';

export const zai = createOpenAI({
  apiKey: process.env.ZAI_API_KEY!,
  baseURL: 'https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4', // general API :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}
});
```

### Call **chat** explicitly

```ts
import { generateText } from 'ai';
import { zai } from './lib/zai-openai';

const { text } = await generateText({
  model: zai.chat('glm-4.7'), // key point: use .chat(...)
  messages: [{ role: 'user', content: 'Explain what an AST is.' }],
});

console.log(text);
```

> If you need Z.AI-specific fields like `thinking`, the **community provider is simpler**, because it already exposes them cleanly. (Z.AI’s native parameter is `thinking.type` with `enabled/disabled`.) ([Z.AI][4])

